Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered) (for 4, zest 1 lemon and quarter both). Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped). In a #small bowl{}, combine parsley, @olive oil{3%tbsp} (5 TBSP for 4), a pinch of garlic and lemon zest, and lemon juice to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; set aside.

Toss @green beans{6%ounce} on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper. Pat @tilapia{11%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; rub all over with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper. Place on empty side of same baking sheet. Roast on top rack until tilapia is cooked through and green beans are tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 baking sheets; roast green beans on top rack and tilapia on middle rack.)

Meanwhile, once water is boiling, add @Israeli Couscous{1/2%cup} to pot. Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain thoroughly. Melt @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tbsp} in empty pot over medium heat. Return couscous to pot and stir until coated. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat; keep covered until ready to serve.

While couscous cooks, heat a #medium pan{}, dry, over medium-high heat. Add @almonds{1/2%ounce} and toast, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, ~{2-4%minutes}. Turn off heat. Transfer to a #cutting board{}; finely chop half the almonds.

Stir chopped almonds into bowl with gremolata. Add a small pinch of @?chili flakes{1%tsp} if desired. Season with salt, pepper, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste.

Divide couscous, green beans, and tilapia between #plates{}. Spoon almond parsley gremolata over tilapia. Scatter remaining almonds over green beans; add a pinch of chili flakes if desired. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> This recipe features a delightful gremolata sauce with almonds, parsley, and lemon that elevates the tilapia to a whole 'lata weeknight goodness.